pan><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/11/elon-musk-mark-zuckerberg-cage-fight-italy-government" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/trump-trial-date-sooner-warns-judge-tanya-chutkan" target="_blank">Inflammatory remarks could speed up 2020 election trial, judge warns Trump</a></h2><div class="description"> Judge Tanya Chutkan rules ex-president free to share ‘non-sensitive materials’ but rejected majority of his other requests. Trump's inflammatory remarks will push her to schedule the trial sooner, she said. Judge Chutkkan ruled on Trump’s requests to have fewer restrictions in a protective order.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 19:25:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/trump-trial-date-sooner-warns-judge-tanya-chutkan" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/conservative-women-tradwife-republican" target="_blank">‘Better martyrs’: the growing role of women in the far-right movement</a></h2><div class="description"> The pipeline from mommy blogger to Tradwife to book-banner is an important aspect of the extreme right wing in the US. Women often work behind the scenes to advance conspiracy theories through social media. But at the same time, in recent years ‘alt-right’ women have also shifted to influential public-facing roles in rightwing media production and far-right national politics.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 10:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/conservative-women-tradwife-republican" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/at-least-two-dead-and-five-missing-after-boat-sinks-off-tunisia" target="_blank">At least two dead and five missing after boat sinks off Tunisia</a></h2><div class="description"> Thirteen people rescued after Europe-bound vessel sank near city of Gabes, says coastguard. Vessel carrying 20 Tunisians went down at 2am 120 metres (395ft) from the beach in Gabes. At least two Tunisians including a baby died when their boat sank off the north African country’s south-eastern shores.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 12:40:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/at-least-two-dead-and-five-missing-after-boat-sinks-off-tunisia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/12/biden-economic-adviser-c-kirabo-jackson-education" target="_blank">Biden choice of economic adviser shows focus on education ahead of 2024 bid</a></h2><div class="description"> Joe Biden taps C Kirabo Jackson, a labor economist known for research on economics and education, for CEA role. Public education will be a key area of focus for Biden’s brain-trust ahead of a 2024 re-election bid. The position does not require Senate confirmation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 13:07:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/12/biden-economic-adviser-c-kirabo-jackson-education" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/gallery/2023/aug/12/the-show-must-go-on-edinburgh-festival-2023-continues-in-pictures" target="_blank">The show must go on! Edinburgh festival 2023 continues – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> Photographer Murdo MacLeod captures the second week of the Edinburgh festival 2023. Murdo captures the Korean twist on Euripides to imaginary friends. See all our Edinburgh festival coverage of the 2023 festival here. Visit Murdo's gallery for more of the festival's coverage of 2023 events.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 16:41:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/gallery/2023/aug/12/the-show-must-go-on-edinburgh-festival-2023-continues-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/12/jo-ann-beard-nothing-in-writing-is-ever-particularly-enjoyable-to-me" target="_blank">Jo Ann Beard: ‘Nothing in writing is ever particularly enjoyable to me’</a></h2><div class="description"> The Collected Works of Jo Ann Beard, 68, is now being published in the UK. The American essayist's most famous collection, The Boys of My Youth, has become a staple of creative writing courses. Serpent’s Tail has brought together Beard's most recent collection, Festival Days, in one book. Beard also published In Zanesville, a novel, in 2011.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 17:00:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/aug/12/jo-ann-beard-nothing-in-writing-is-ever-particularly-enjoyable-to-me" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/12/tulisa-ive-definitely-been-a-victim-of-classism-" target="_blank">Tulisa: ‘I’ve definitely been a victim of classism’</a></h2><div class="description"> Singer, 35, talks about escaping from childhood, living with Bell's palsy, that sex tape release and the highs and lows of fame. Singing gave me the power I’d been missing to take control of my own life, she says. Singer's dad was in the band Mungo Jerry, and her mum was in an Andrews Sisters-style harmonising group.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 13:02:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/12/tulisa-ive-definitely-been-a-victim-of-classism-" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/12/the-rest-is-football-podcast-gary-lineker-alan-shearer-micah-richards-terribly-famous-adele-file-on-four-jon-holmes-generation-shame-this-cultural-life-stephen-fry" target="_blank">The week in audio: The Rest is Football; Terribly Famous; File on 4: Jon Holmes, Generation Shame; This Cultural Life</a></h2><div class="description"> Gary Lineker tackles some offside topics in his new podcast, while a celebrity series discusses all things Adele. Plus, Jon Holmes on the painful search for his birth parents, and the return of a Radio 4 favourite. Alastair Campbell and Rory Stewart sell out the Royal Albert Hall faster than the Foo Fighters.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 16:00:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/12/the-rest-is-football-podcast-gary-lineker-alan-shearer-micah-richards-terribly-famous-adele-file-on-four-jon-holmes-generation-shame-this-cultural-life-stephen-fry" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/12/rose-matafeo-starstruck-interview" target="_blank">Rose Matafeo: ‘I feel a massive sense of guilt for making a romcom’</a></h2><div class="description"> The 31-year-old New-Zealand-born comic breathed new life into her smash hit Starstruck. She's now wondering whether it’s done more harm than good. The series returns for a third run this summer, with a third episode set to be released.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 10:55:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/12/rose-matafeo-starstruck-interview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/12/classical-musicians-are-clone-like-these-days-says-nigel-kennedy" target="_blank">Classical musicians are ‘clone-like’ these days, says Nigel Kennedy</a></h2><div class="description"> Renowned violinist applauds the technical proficiency of young players although he finds new teaching methods a ‘brain and heart turn-off’ Young classical musicians starting out in their careers are sacrificing creativity and individuality and becoming ‘clone-like’, says Nigel Kennedy.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 14:17:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/12/classical-musicians-are-clone-like-these-days-says-nigel-kennedy" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/the-toughest-qualification-in-finance-why-its-now-more-achievable-than-ever" target="_blank">The toughest qualification in finance? Why it’s now more achievable than ever</a></h2><div class="description"> The CFA charter is considered the gold standard for those seeking to work in finance. But it has long been regarded as notoriously challenging – now, it’s become more accessible and appealing to a broader range of applicants. 60 years since candidates sat the first exams, the CFA Program has changed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:41:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/the-toughest-qualification-in-finance-why-its-now-more-achievable-than-ever" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/fighting-fires-with-finance-how-investment-professionals-can-help-tackle-the-climate-emergency" target="_blank">Fighting fires with finance: how investment professionals can help tackle the climate emergency</a></h2><div class="description"> As the climate crisis becomes impossible to ignore, the world of finance is waking up to the risks it poses. These include the devastating effects of a warming planet, the regulatory impact of the global transition to a low-carbon economy, and the reputational risk of being a laggard in the eyes of eco-conscious consumers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:31:11 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/fighting-fires-with-finance-how-investment-professionals-can-help-tackle-the-climate-emergency" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/from-crypto-sleuth-to-carbon-cutter-five-little-known-jobs-you-can-do-as-a-chartered-financial-analyst" target="_blank">From crypto sleuth to carbon cutter: five little-known jobs you can do as a chartered financial analyst</a></h2><div class="description"> Chartered financial analysts typically go into the financial sector at an investment firm. But there are a number of less familiar career paths that can be taken too. About half of the world’s portfolio managers are CFA charterholders, according to CFA Institute. Here are five lesser-known career paths you can take too.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:40:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/from-crypto-sleuth-to-carbon-cutter-five-little-known-jobs-you-can-do-as-a-chartered-financial-analyst" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/invest-in-your-future-why-a-career-in-finance-can-make-a-positive-impact-on-the-world" target="_blank">Invest in your future: why a career in finance can make a positive impact on the world</a></h2><div class="description"> The finance sector has long been thought of as problematic when it comes to the impact it has on society. But things are changing – financiers are increasingly starting to tackle pressing problems such as the climate crisis and inequality. The global transition to clean energy and a low carbon economy requires a massive reallocation of resources, while the widespread embrace of so-called ESG factors has proved to be a genuine paradi.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 14 Jul 2023 10:31:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/a-charter-for-change/2023/jul/14/invest-in-your-future-why-a-career-in-finance-can-make-a-positive-impact-on-the-world" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/12/charleston-house-how-fashion-world-fell-for-bloomsbury-set-country-home" target="_blank">Bohemian rhapsody: how the fashion world fell for Charleston, the Bloomsbury set’s country farmhouse</a></h2><div class="description"> Charleston is a thickset farmhouse of doughty 17th-century stone, scrambled with roses. The layout is warren-like rather than open plan, the floors unevenly boarded. Every room is decorated by hand, in dizzying detail – sponge-painted diamonds on wood panelling.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 10:00:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/12/charleston-house-how-fashion-world-fell-for-bloomsbury-set-country-home" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/12/button-up-minimalist-waistcoats-for-women" target="_blank">Button up: minimalist waistcoats for women</a></h2><div class="description"> The waistcoat-and-trousers co-ord cut a polished silhouette on SS23 runways. Coperni embraced the noughties vibe with a fitted, pinstripe waistcoat styled with baggy cargos. Celine came over all Kate Moss and Sienna Miller with a leather waistcoat layered over a striped top.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 22:45:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/fashion/2023/aug/12/button-up-minimalist-waistcoats-for-women" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/13/its-become-a-lot-more-like-a-share-house-when-adult-children-stay-in-the-parental-home" target="_blank">‘It’s become a lot more like a share house’: when adult children stay in the parental home</a></h2><div class="description"> Young people are increasingly staying at home longer, and more often moving back with parents as adults. Ben, 23, says he has 'no real reason' to move out of his parent's home. The architecture student's mountaineering and ice climbing gear fills every spare space.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 20:00:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/13/its-become-a-lot-more-like-a-share-house-when-adult-children-stay-in-the-parental-home" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/12/an-exhilarating-travel-adventure-in-northumberland-england" target="_blank">Everything was reduced to wind, water and me: an exhilarating adventure in Northumberland</a></h2><div class="description"> Our writer heads to north-east England to go coasteering, rockpooling and wing surfing – with dolphins and puffins offering moral support. He heads to the area to go wing surfing and rockpool with dolphins, puffins and dolphins. Kevin Anderson explains how he uses a foil board to power a hand-held inflatable wing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 13:00:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/12/an-exhilarating-travel-adventure-in-northumberland-england" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/12/how-six-uk-couples-manage-family-finances-now-the-pressure-is-on" target="_blank">How six UK couples manage family finances now the pressure is on</a></h2><div class="description"> 35% of UK couples admitted that financial pressures had put a strain on their relationship. 28% of respondents said that the cost of living crisis had led to them arguing about money more frequently. The squeeze on finances has taken its toll on some couples, whether it is the strain caused by higher housing costs or disagreements about reining in spending.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 09:00:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/12/how-six-uk-couples-manage-family-finances-now-the-pressure-is-on" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/12/life-with-my-hearing-impaired-father" target="_blank">‘I thought of all the times I’d had to shout and my heart shrivelled up’: life with my hearing-impaired father</a></h2><div class="description"> Author Katherine Heiny took her father for a hearing test after an episode of The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills prompted her to take him for a test. Their relationship was marked by confusion and frustration until the test. For him, every conversation was muted and indistinct, an exercise in frustration.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 08:00:12 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/12/life-with-my-hearing-impaired-father" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/10/niger-coup-why-do-so-many-want-france-out-and-russia-in-video-explainer" target="_blank">Niger coup: why do so many want France out and Russia in? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> On 26 July, a group of soldiers removed Niger's democratically elected president from power citing security concerns and economic mismanagement. Crowds waved Russian flags and chanted slogans against France, the country's former coloniser. The anti-French – and more widely anti-foreign – sentiment has rapidly become a key element of how the coup is being framed.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 13:37:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/aug/10/niger-coup-why-do-so-many-want-france-out-and-russia-in-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2023/aug/09/extreme-weather-glacial-flooding-wildfires-and-hailstorms-cause-havoc-across-the-world-video" target="_blank">Extreme weather: glacial flooding, wildfires and hailstorms cause havoc across the world  – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Countries across the globe are facing a range of extreme weather events. Severe flooding has affected parts of Europe including Sweden and Slovenia. Human-caused climate change is supercharging extreme weather across the world, driving more frequent and more deadly disasters, from heatwaves to floods to wildfires.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:36:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/video/2023/aug/09/extreme-weather-glacial-flooding-wildfires-and-hailstorms-cause-havoc-across-the-world-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/luton-fans-share-your-mood-before-the-clubs-first-premier-league-game" target="_blank">Luton fans: share your mood before the club’s first Premier League game</a></h2><div class="description"> Luton Town return to the Premier League for the first time in 31 years. The Hatters face Brighton at the top of the table on Saturday afternoon. Luton fans want to know how excited they are about their chances. Do you have any memories of the last time you were in the top flight?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 11:28:36 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/11/luton-fans-share-your-mood-before-the-clubs-first-premier-league-game" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-employees-how-will-you-be-affected-by-the-retailer-entering-administration" target="_blank">Wilko employees: how will you be affected by the retailer entering administration?</a></h2><div class="description"> More than 12,000 jobs at risk after struggling to agree a rescue deal. The family-owned household and garden products retailer is expected to close dozens of outlets. We want to hear from workers at Wilko following the news that dozens of stores are expected to shut.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:04:55 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2023/aug/10/wilko-employees-how-will-you-be-affected-by-the-retailer-entering-administration" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/people-in-maui-how-have-you-been-affected-by-the-wildfires" target="_blank">People in Maui: how have you been affected by the wildfires?</a></h2><div class="description"> At least 53 people have died in wildfires on the Hawaiian island of Maui. The fires, fanned by strong winds from Hurricane Dora, destroyed businesses in the historic town of Lahaina. There have been 13 evacuations for three fires and at least two dozen people injured.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 09:15:39 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/10/people-in-maui-how-have-you-been-affected-by-the-wildfires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/uk-mortgage-holders-share-your-experience-of-rising-costs" target="_blank">UK mortgage holders: share your experience of repossession</a></h2><div class="description"> There have been 13 consecutive increases in mortgage interest rates placing further strain on homeowners already struggling with soaring bills. We would like to hear from people who are struggling with their mortgage payments and are facing repossession. The ongoing cost of living crisis has placed a growing burden on UK households.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 08:36:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/10/uk-mortgage-holders-share-your-experience-of-rising-costs" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/how-search-for-ufos-reached-us-congress-podcast" target="_blank">How the search for UFOs reached the US Congress – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The quest to discover whether or not we're alone in the universe has become an obsession for many Americans. Now it has gone beyond internet forums, YouTube channels and kooky podcasts. Pentagon has said pilots are seeing things up in the sky that they can’t explain. A few weeks ago, spaceships got their day in Congress.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 02:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/how-search-for-ufos-reached-us-congress-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/12/womens-football-weekly-lionesses-to-face-matildas-in-semi-final-clash" target="_blank">Women’s Football Weekly: Lionesses to face Matildas in semi-final clash</a></h2><div class="description"> England come from behind to knock out Colombia in the World Cup quarter-finals. They’ll face co-hosts Australia in the semi-final. The Matildas needed penalty shootout against France to progress to the last four of the tournament. It is the first time Australia have reached a World Cup semi-finals in their history.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 20:17:59 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/12/womens-football-weekly-lionesses-to-face-matildas-in-semi-final-clash" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/aug/12/weekend-podcast-author-jacqueline-wilson-marina-hyde-on-matt-hancock-as-just-ken-and-is-snacking-a-problem" target="_blank">Weekend podcast: author Jacqueline Wilson, Marina Hyde on Matt Hancock as ‘just Ken’, and is snacking a problem?</a></h2><div class="description"> Marina Hyde recoils at Matt Hancock’s latest cringeworthy attempt to boost his brand. Joel Snape asks Joel Snape whether we should worry about snacking. Simon Hattenstone sits down with Jacqueline Wilson to discuss rivalry, censorship – and love –.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 04:00:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/audio/2023/aug/12/weekend-podcast-author-jacqueline-wilson-marina-hyde-on-matt-hancock-as-just-ken-and-is-snacking-a-problem" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/11/power-junk-food-companies-washington-podcast" target="_blank">The power of junk food companies in Washington – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Jonathan Freedland speaks to Dr Eduardo J Gómez of Lehigh University, on how his new book Junk Food Politics taught him about the power of lobbyists. He also discusses the growing rate of obesity in the US, why are politicians not stepping in to improve nutrition?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 04:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/audio/2023/aug/11/power-junk-food-companies-washington-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/best-of-2023-so-far-i-know-where-the-bodies-are-buried-one-womans-mission-to-change-how-the-police-investigate-podcast" target="_blank">Best of 2023… so far: ‘I know where the bodies are buried’: one woman’s mission to change how the police investigate rape – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Every Friday in August we will publish some of our favourite audio long reads of 2023. This week, Betsy Stanko leads an investigation into why the police have been failing so badly to tackle sexual violence. But is there any chance of fixing a system that seems so broken?</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 04:00:26 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/11/best-of-2023-so-far-i-know-where-the-bodies-are-buried-one-womans-mission-to-change-how-the-police-investigate-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/10/premier-league-season-preview-liverpool-to-wolves-football-weekly" target="_blank">Premier League season preview: Liverpool to Wolves – Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Max Rushden is joined by Barry Glendenning, Jonathan Wilson and Mark Langdon for our second Premier League preview show. The panel ponder whether Liverpool can plug a hole in their midfield and get themselves back among the top four. They also discuss how Manchester United and Newcastle will fare with the added rigour of Champions League football to contend with.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 11:48:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/10/premier-league-season-preview-liverpool-to-wolves-football-weekly" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/12/spicy-fish-balls-pepper-chilli-sauce-recipe-honey-and-co" target="_blank">Honey & Co’s recipe for spicy fish balls in pepper chilli sauce</a></h2><div class="description"> The right amount of heat is needed to bring out the flavours, and where too much will kill them instead. This is one such: tender fishballs with a delicate but assertive seasoning of fresh coriander in a juicy, fruity, peppery sauce. The fishball stew could be your new favourite weeknight supper.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 09:00:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/12/spicy-fish-balls-pepper-chilli-sauce-recipe-honey-and-co" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/12/can-britain-create-a-microchip-industry-worth-its-salt" target="_blank">Can Britain recreate a microchip industry worth its salt?</a></h2><div class="description"> UK governments let processor manufacturing drift overseas for years. Covid and war have shown how vital homegrown capability is, the country is scrambling to catch up. But so is everyone else, and so are everyone else. The UK government is scrambling for a way of catching up with globalisation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 15:02:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/business/2023/aug/12/can-britain-create-a-microchip-industry-worth-its-salt" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/12/astrophysicist-sarafina-el-badry-nance-starstruck-memoir-astrophysics-light-dark" target="_blank">Astrophysicist Sarafina El-Badry Nance: ‘I’ll probably always live with impostor syndrome’</a></h2><div class="description"> Egyptian-American astrophysicist Sarafina El-Badry Nance's debut memoir, Starstruck, is about growing up to be a scientist today as a woman of colour. Nance, 30, is a passionate communicator of cosmology and advocate for women’s health.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 12:00:17 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/2023/aug/12/astrophysicist-sarafina-el-badry-nance-starstruck-memoir-astrophysics-light-dark" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/china-deflation-ticking-time-bomb" target="_blank">Behind the ticking time bomb – should we fear China’s slide into deflation?</a></h2><div class="description"> China was expected to roar back into life after Covid-19 pandemic, but its weak rebound has shocked analysts. Consumer prices index fell by 0.3% compared with 2022, while producer prices fell by 4.4%. It is the first time that both figures have been negative since November 2020.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Sat, 12 Aug 2023 05:00:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/china-deflation-ticking-time-bomb" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/between-two-worlds-life-of-png-tribe-leader-and-plantation-owner-honoured" target="_blank">Between two worlds: life of PNG tribe leader and plantation owner honoured</a></h2><div class="description"> Joe Leahy, owner of the famed Kilima coffee plantation, remembered in week-long traditional ceremony in Papua New Guinea. Kilima was purchased from the Ganiga in the early 1970s by a then young Johannes ‘Joe’ Leahy. He spent years building up and then decades mourning its destruction. Earlier this month Leahy died, aged 85, inside the house he lived in most of his life.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 20:00:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/12/between-two-worlds-life-of-png-tribe-leader-and-plantation-owner-honoured" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/biden-climate-bill-inflation-reduction-act" target="_blank">Green investment boom and electric car sales: six key things about Biden’s climate bill</a></h2><div class="description"> The $369bn Inflation Reduction Act has boosted clean energy and EV cars. Joe Biden hailed the bill as ‘one of the most significant laws in our history’ when signing it on 16 August last year. The bill is both lauded for turbocharging a seismic shift to clean energy while also weathering attack from Republicans.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Fri, 11 Aug 2023 10:00:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/11/biden-climate-bill-inflation-reduction-act" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Sign up for the Fashion Statement newsletter: our free fashion email</a></h2><div class="description"> Style, with substance: what’s really trending this week, a roundup of the best fashion journalism and your wardrobe dilemmas solved, delivered straight to your inbox every Thursday. Find out what's really trending and what you need to look at this week's top fashion stories.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 20 Sep 2022 11:06:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Click here 